01:04:03.139 --> 01:04:04.619
Prof: What the function
of light here?

01:04:04.619 --> 01:04:14.088
Well, the--I can give you a
little bit of the idea of what

01:04:14.088 --> 01:04:23.059
we call the metaphysics of light
in Paradiso.

01:04:23.059 --> 01:04:30.512
Dante begins with the idea that
what we know of the divine is

01:04:30.512 --> 01:04:34.485
light,
a light that--the power of

01:04:34.485 --> 01:04:40.748
which and the limitation of
which is exactly like the dark

01:04:40.748 --> 01:04:47.010
in the sense that the light
reveals to us the divine,

01:04:47.010 --> 01:04:50.699
but at the same time hides the
origin of the light.

01:04:50.699 --> 01:04:52.210
You cannot see through the
light.

01:04:52.210 --> 01:04:58.063
That's really the understanding
of Dante in Paradiso I

01:04:58.063 --> 01:05:00.492
saying,
"The glory of Him who

01:05:00.492 --> 01:05:03.340
moves all things,"
the glory is an image really

01:05:03.340 --> 01:05:04.179
means light.
 

01:05:04.179 --> 01:05:07.206
The light of Him,
who moves all things,

01:05:07.206 --> 01:05:09.039
is what I really saw.
 

01:05:09.039 --> 01:05:12.802
Now Dante's seeing the origin
of that light,

01:05:12.802 --> 01:05:18.141
that which has remained forever
invisible, exactly the way the

01:05:18.141 --> 01:05:19.280
dark has.
 

01:05:19.280 --> 01:05:23.956
You may say that some of our
imagination is that we are in

01:05:23.956 --> 01:05:24.860
the dark.
 

01:05:24.860 --> 01:05:28.010
We don't know the origins of
anything;

01:05:28.010 --> 01:05:32.860
we don't know the causes that
lie beyond our perceptions.

01:05:32.860 --> 01:05:36.748
We don't know the origin of the
dark, we may even go like

01:05:36.748 --> 01:05:39.804
mystics believing that the dark
is the image,

01:05:39.804 --> 01:05:41.679
is the cover for light.
 

01:05:41.679 --> 01:05:44.750
If there is a dark there must
be a light somewhere else,

01:05:44.750 --> 01:05:47.429
in fact that dark may
occasionally be removed.

01:05:47.429 --> 01:05:51.284
The worst thing about the
mystical language of the divine

01:05:51.284 --> 01:05:54.449
in terms of light is that the
light itself,

01:05:54.449 --> 01:05:57.983
which makes all things visible,
remains in and of itself

01:05:57.983 --> 01:06:00.940
impenetrable in its origin to
the human eye.

01:06:00.940 --> 01:06:04.070
Now Dante sees it,
that's the idea of the true

01:06:04.070 --> 01:06:07.619
light, "In thy light we see
the light."

01:06:07.619 --> 01:06:10.632
Is that a little--
Student:  The beatific

